What is EngeneIC?



EnGeneIC is a biotech company with a proprietary EDV™ nanocell platform for the targeted delivery of chemotherapeutics and functional nucleic acids in cancer. Their patented technology makes cancer treatment more potent and far less toxic.

Beyond oncology, EnGeneIC’s EDV™ has the potential to be used in vulnerable COVID-19 patients and other future viral pandemics, with the company planning to start human trials in Australia for this purpose.

Problem and Market

Cancer is a leading cause of death worldwide, with over 10 million deaths caused in 2020 globally (World Health Organisation, 2021) and over 19 million new cancer cases reported that same year (GLOBOCAN, 2020). Beyond the unmeasurable impact that this disease has had on individuals and families globally, the global economic impact was calculated at USD 113 billion in 2016 and is expected to grow annually in the range of 6% to 9% annually (Market Reports World, 2018). In the United States, where most of the data is available, this figure was calculated to be at USD 183 billion in 2015 and projected to grow to USD 246 billion by 2030, or a 34% increase (American Cancer Society, 2020).

The oncology market was valued at $136 billion in 2019 and is forecasted to grow at a CAGR of 11.9% between 2020-2025 (Research and Markets, 2020). Global Market Insights forecasts this industry to reach a valuation of over $469 billion by 2026. Asia Pacific holds a substantial part of that growth, with a forecasted 11.4% CAGR through the coming years due to a large patient pool in highly populated countries that are vulnerable to different cancers (Global Market Insights, 2021).

This patient population has very limited treatment options, with very few in the market. This is particularly the case for late-stage cancer.

EnGeneIC Solution: EnGeneIC Dream Vector (EDV)

EnGeneIC has developed a unique patent-protected biotechnology called EDV™ which stands for EnGeneIC Deam Vector. This oncological biotech application provides cancer treatment that is more potent and far less toxic than others in the market.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Their EDV™ solution is exceedingly complicated and completely new in the world. The EDV™ effectively works as a vehicle for highly targeted nano cells that carry an anti-cancer drug. These nano cells are designed to identify proteins that are found on the cancer cell surface. Blood vessels surrounding the cancer are all very defective, with large openings in their walls. The EDV™ nanocells will drop out of these holes and get into the cancer environment. The cancer cell will then be provoked to swallow the entire EDV™, attacking the cancerogenic cell like a trojan horse.


In addition to being active agents that attack cancer cells, these EDV™ cells serve the dual purpose of activating our natural killer cells. In patients with advanced cancer stages, these immune system cells being to become suppressed, to the point that they are no longer able to fight cancer cells. EnGeneIC addresses this by enabling the EDV™ cells to be attractive to our natural killer cells, and these immune system cells will re-activate when they come across EDV™ cells as they identify them as bacterial origin. The result is our natural killer cells become aggressive and start attacking the living cancer cells.


The battle against cancer is started by the EDV™cells, and it ensures a lasting impact by activating other natural killer cells such as the Macrophage and Dendritic cells, which will then, in turn, call the highly aggressive cytotoxic T cells to join the battle against the remaining living cancer cells.

Competitive Advantage

EnGeneIC is currently the only company in the world to have achieved this dual battle against cancer with one single technology. Most other leading cancer treatments rely largely on attacking cancer cells. However, as the past 60 years of cancer science have proven, this method becomes ineffective as the cancer cells mutate and become resistant to the poison.

The other type of leading treatment is trying to reactivate our natural killer cells to fight cancerogenic cells. However, this solution alone tends to be a patchwork and it will only work in a small percentage of patients.

EnGeneIC, with one single technology, is using their EDV™ technology as a decoy to both attack cancer cells directly while simultaneously reactivating our natural killer cells to join the fight, making it a much more comprehensive treatment against cancer, particularly in the late stages of this disease.

EnGeneIC has 435 granted patents in this space, with 67 more pending. Beyond the previously explained unique technology, their competitive advantage is built on:

  • Product Advantage: Highly efficacious, safe and unique product, which has already been developed.

  • Very large target market: The applications of this technology are vast, with the EDV™ technology applicable to nearly all solid tumors and with an extensive global pool of patients due to Cancer’s pervasive growth over the past decades. Furthermore, EnGeneIC is now beginning to apply this technology for human trials to treat pandemic viral diseases such as Covid-19. The first trials are set to begin soon and if successful, this would exponentially increase the total addressable market of their patent-protected product.

  • Low Cost of Goods: EnGeneIC’s cost of manufacturing is very low, while their processes and know-how are readily transferable to large pharmaceutical companies.

  • Straightforward logistics: This biotechnology does not require cold chain in transport, making it easy to ship and store. In addition, their product has a long shelf life of 3+years.

  • Extensive Patent Portfolio: As the sole owner of 435 granted patents and with 67 more pending, EnGeneIC’s valuation as an innovative biotech has astonishing potential, particularly as it readies for IPO in NASDAQ in early 2022.

  • Absence of Competition: The growing global pool of patients has no alternative treatment to what EnGeneIC has developed, providing them with a blue ocean of growth vs the currently leading treatments.

In addition, EnGeneIC has a well-established engagement with most major US pharmaceutical companies and investment banks in the USA. This is critical as they prepare for a public listing in NASDAQ

Growth Strategy

Venture Capital deal activity within biotech and biopharma in 2020 notched a record $28.5 billion of capital across 1,073 deals. This represents a 60.5% year-over-year increase in deal value over 2019’s aggregate $17.8 billion—the most significant YoY increase to date (PitchBook, 2021).

The IPO market for VC-backed biotech companies has yet to cool down. In 2020, IPOs by VC-backed biotech companies raised $11.5 billion in capital across 73 biotech public listings, with total exit value reaching a record $37.3 billion. The median biotech IPO exit size also surged to a record $451.1 million, representing a 34.5% YoY increase over 2019’s median of $335.3 million (PitchBook, 2021).

EnGeneIC has demonstrated remarkable results in the BioTech industry. Some of these successes include:

  • Significantly extended survival time for patients with life expectancy of just a few weeks – 2 years & more

  • Efficacy against several major and rare cancers

  • Over 1,800 doses delivered to 160 patients to date

  • Minimal to no toxic side effects

  • Only technology that has shown efficacy in COVID-vulnerable patients i.e. elderly and immuno-compromised (highest risk of death in this population if they are not treated)

  • Targeting ‘Breakthrough Drug’ status for cancer therapeutics & for COVID-19

  • Lowest cost of goods among any other novel cancer therapeutic & hence affordable world-wide

Due to their proven results, EnGeneIC has reiceved over $80 million equity funding in previous rounds, largely from institutional and sophisticated investors across Australia, New Zealand, Singapore and the US. In addition, they have received over $10 million in government funding.

Exit Strategy

An investment in EngenIC is well positioned to take advantage of of one of two major liquidity events available to the breakthrough BioTech firm:

Public Listing - NASDAQ IPO

  • EnGeneIC is working with major banks in the USA to prepare for the NASDAQ pre-IPO, targeting Q2 2022.

  • Senior partners with IPO experience at Latham Watkins LLC (New York) are working on the preparation of S1.

  • All the finances have been converted from Australian accounting to US GAAP accounting to comply with NASDAQ requirements.

  • CFO is Mr William Harris (New York office) who is experienced in NASDAQ listed companies.

  • COO is Mr David Seaton, who is also experienced in NASDAQ listed companies.

  • EnGeneIC is currently seeking to appoint a couple of stellar names on the Board who have successfully listed BioTech companies on NASDAQ.

  • Board Directors, Dr Merv Turner was the ex-head of licensing at Merck (USA), Yvonne Perlberg was ex-finance auditor (12 years) on the Amgen Board (world’s largest BioTech company, USA), Dr. Levitt was ex-head of Oncology at TEVA pharmaceuticals and Prof. Bryan Williams was Chairman of NASDAQ listed successful Australian BioTech company.

Major Pharma Acquisition

  • The investment banks in the US are taking a dual-track approach which is either an IPO or a significant Pharma acquisition.

  • Given EnGeneIC’s stellar clinical results in completely unmet oncology needs, there is a high likelihood that Pharma acquisition could occur pre-IPO or soon after.

  • Performance Fee: 20% of profit. We only charge a performance fee on conversion or exit.

  • A commercially significant new application of the EDV technology, COVID-19 Therapeutic/Vaccine for the COVID-vulnerable population was invented and shown to be successful in pre-clinical and clinical setting.

  • Worldwide patent applications were filed and shown to be globally unique approach in treatment of COVID-vulnerable population where no other vaccine has been shown to work. This will add new value to the IPO

Phase IIa clinical trial in pancreatic and other cancers continued to show stellar results in terms of stabilization/regression of cancers in end-stage cancer patients, absence of toxic side effects and a dramatic increase in overall survival.

Risks

Investing in private companies is risky. Issuers using this facility include new or rapidly growing ventures. Investment in these types of ventures is speculative and carries high risks. You may lose your entire investment, and you should be in a position to bear this risk without undue hardship. Even if the company is successful, the value of your investment and any return on the investment could be reduced if the company issues more shares. Your investment is unlikely to be liquid. This means you are unlikely to be able to sell your shares quickly or at all if you need the money or decide that this investment is not right for you. Even though you have remedies for misleading statements in the offer document or misconduct by the company, you may have difficulty recovering your money. There are rules for handling your money. However, if your money is handled inappropriately or the person operating this platform becomes insolvent, you may have difficulty recovering your money. Ask questions, read all information given carefully, and seek independent financial advice before committing yourself to any investment.
